features: 【Relief the Pain】The lumbar support pillow used ergonomic design is adopted to fill the gap between the waist and the bed, fit the curve of the lumbar spine, and effectively relieve the pain caused by the waist, thereby reducing the burden on the back.

【Multifunction Lumbar Support Pillow】Our memory foam backrest lumbar support pillow can be used in multiple places. Whether as lumbar support for cars, or as back support for recliners/beds, it offers top comfort anytime.

【Soft and Breathable】The back cushion used rebound memory foam can provide you with comfort for a long time, and achieve a proper balance between support and comfort. The 4D mesh fabric keeps your back cool and dry.

【Rthopedic Doctor Recommened】High density memory foam lower back pillow with ergonomic streamline is recommended by orthopedic doctors for lower back and hip pain relief. It is thin and makes your driving more comfortable rather than thick ones that will push you off your seat.

【Warm Tips】For optimal appearance and support, please unpack it and wait more than 24 hours until it is fully inflated. In terms of hardness, note that it varies from temperature to temperature, becoming harder at cold temperatures but instantly softer when placed in warm conditions, so this is normal and does not affect use. If you encounter any problems during use, please feel free to contact us, and we will provide you with return and exchange services.

reviews.reviewText: When I had surgery I had to sleep on my back for 4-6 weeks. I’m a side or stomach sleeper because of bad back pain. While this didn’t give me a super comfortable night, it definitely made the time tolerable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the long haul
reviews.reviewText: Driving and older, yet comfortable vehicle 17 hours, this was a back saver for lumbar support. It’s firm as other reviewers mentioned, and I believe that’s the point in having a lumbar pillow for the car/truck.Where I typically get out to stretch and feel achey, using this really helped to keep me aligned while driving. I didn’t find it to be too bulky, but did find that moving the seat back a little helped with getting everything aligned properly.

I have been having back problems and purchased this for work. It is a nice size and I use it all day. Works great and helps with some of the pain.

reviews.reviewTitle: Turns stone hard in cold weather
reviews.reviewText: Worked great until the weather turned cold (freezing, zero degrees Celsius and below) at which point it turns into a stone hard blob. So if you are blessed with above zero temperatures all year around, it is a fine product. If you have cold winters and you want to keep using it in your car, it's not going to work.
